result.name: Rubato Music House Bar & Kitchen

reviews.text: Charming small restaurant/bar, atmosphere inspired to the music and cinema world of the past, provinding an italian/western offering (pizza included) with a good level of service. Comfortable to reach, 5 minutes walk far from MTR Olympic (exit B). Pleasant live music, never such to overwhelm clients. Several flat screen TVs, showing premium films and maybe also sport events. Good choice of wines, also European ones. Prices adequate to service.
Wonderful place for wine, for gossip, for music....
Lunch set price is reasonable.

It's my first time in Hong Kong and in the time that my mate and I have been here, this by far is the best restaurant we have dined in because of the delicious food, live entertainment, good pricing and exceptional service by the staff.  We have tried other restaurants but were disappointed due to the fact of the language barrier plus the food were not that impressive. I truly recommend 'Rubato' to those who stay around Mong Kok.
Cosy place, nice food and music
